avalancheActivity.highlights: Moist snow slides are possible from the middle of the day.
avalancheActivity.comment: The early morning will see favourable avalanche conditions generally. As the day progresses on very steep sunny slopes there will be only a slight increase in the danger of moist snow slides. The avalanches can be released by people or triggered naturally.

snowpackStructure.comment:
On Saturday in extremely steep terrain numerous small and, in isolated cases, medium-sized avalanches occurred naturally, in particular avalanches with origins in high-altitude starting zones.
As a consequence of falling temperatures and low relative humidity a crust will form on the surface during the night. These conditions will foster a substantial stabilisation of the snowpack in all aspects.
Above approximately 2000 m there are 20 to 30 cm of snow, and even more in some localities. At low altitude from a snow sport perspective, insufficient snow is lying.

tendency.highlights: Tuesday: The danger of moist snow slides will persist.
